The organizational documents of entities in which we have an equity-method investment generally require periodic distributions
of their available cash to their members. In each case, available cash is reduced, in part, by reserves appropriate for operating their
respective businesses. See Note 9 – Investing Activities of Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements for our more significant equity-
method investees.
